</TD></TR></TABLE></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uonyxrosevalsharess.showPublicProfile?language=EN>OnyxroseValSharess</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/22/02 4:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Make Containers Wearable!</span><hr size=1> Last time this question was officially asked, the answer was something along the lines of....<br>
<br>
Each &quot;character&quot; entry on the server has a fixed data structure, such that you have 21 slots on the body, 8 inventory slots, and I believe 4 on the cursor.  Each of the 8 inventory slots can have up to a 10 slot bag.  In addition to that, add 8 bank slots at max 10 each.  That makes 181 slots per character, plus more on the cursor, though I'm not certain that cursor items stay with you...<br>
<br>
Next, how much data space does each slot take up?  Figure that each item in the game can be represented by an ID Number, of which I'm guesstimating is a Unsigned Long Integer (4 bytes).  Then, each item has a &quot;count&quot; associated with it, which is max 20 for players, but significantly larger on vendors, so we can guess that they are saving space with an Unsigned Short Integer (2 bytes).    Total: 6 bytes per slot.<br>
<br>
So, a quick guess gives us 181 x 6, or 1086 bytes per character just to hold inventory information.  <br>
<br>
Allowing one &quot;wearable&quot; inventory slot to equip a 10-slot container will require an extra 60 bytes, because you have to have room in the character profile even if a bag isn't equipped, or even if the bag is &quot;empty&quot; (an empty bag isn't really empty, its full of items with ID # 0, Count 0).  <br>
<br>
If we want the ability to put a container in ANY slot, that's 21x10x6, or 1260 additional bytes required to hold items.<br>
<br>
Each player can have 8 characters per server, so we have to increase our data useage by 10080 bytes per player account per server.  <br>
<br>
10k bytes per player doesn't seem like much... but how many characters are there per server?  We could estimate 2500 active players, lets bump it up to 4000 unique players per server over the course of 24 hours.  That means you've increased the character database by a minimum of 40,320,000 bytes per server, which comes out to about 38.5 MB.<br>
<br>
That was the easy part, now you have to recode all of your servers to accept the new character profile... that means the server has to allow the new inventory slots to hold items, then it has to recognize how to place items into and remove items from the bags.  All that stuff is done on the server side to prevent hacks...<br>
<br>
Then you have to rebuild ALL of the character profiles to increase the base size, which invalidates ALL of your old backups, since the backups wont be the same data structure.  Every time I ever needed items returned in the past, they had to restore my entire profile from tape; Verant isn't using a &quot;real&quot; database, they have their own pared down, non-transaction custom DB, so who knows how it really handles restorations..<br>
<br>
Next you add a whole host of inventory-slot restricted containers to the item database, add the items to vendor inventories and/or the drop-lists of monsters.<br>
<br>
Then you have to worry about increased bandwidth issues, since you've just increased the character profile by 1k... that will make zoning slightly slower (server to server transfers), and more lag when character info is sent to clients.<br>
<br>
<br>
The end result is that any change to the character profile would be extremely risky, would cause a lot of fundamental changes to the entire structure of EQ, and simply would require a lot of programming work....  I wouldnt expect it to happen any time soon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujarnin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 1589<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/23/02 3:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Make Containers Wearable!</span><hr size=1> /me is humbled by the lady from Blood Coven <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>(Title left blank)</span><br>  Posts: 4966<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/24/02 7:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> bags etc</span><hr size=1> Just a little note, thanks for the technical thoughts, Onyxrose ValSharess.  However, there was in fact a bag that could be equipped a few months back.  It functioned as a bag, and could be swapped in and out of the slot it was placed in as well as items put in and out of it.<br>
<br>
In other words, the code wouldn't have to change other than flagging what goes where, it's already in the game clearly or this wouldn't be possible.<br>
<br>
As I pointed out before, however, if you had to put wrist pouches on your wrist the you couldn't put ANYTHING ELSE THERE.  This includes Opal Bracelets and Supple Scale Armbands and what all you have there right now.  The present equipment system allows you to put a bag on your 'wrist' as well as a wrist item.<br>
<br>
The only slot they should change is the ammo slot, which begs in such a blatantly obvious way for quivers it hurts to look at.  Allowing people to equip quivers in this one spot would limit what kind of bag, what area, and even what kind of items that could be put in it.  It would also make quivers valuable now, instead of only for Rangers at level 60. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=686.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=686.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=686.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.threadControl?topicID=686.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=686.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=686.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=